The data set presented in this report is a collection of radio data from 2014. It contains a weeks worth of songs played across 25 radio stations that play rock music. This data was collected to answer an analysis on what categorizes a song as classic rock because over time the definition has changed, we hope to achieve this analysis by computing the frequency of songs played by rock bands from the 1960s to early 2000s which is considered the tail end of the rock era. The data set is stored as a CSV file, delimited by a comma.

The bar chart below depicts the top 10 most played rock songs on the 3rd week of June 2014 by 25 different rock radio stations

Attached is the below line chart for the number of times AC/DC was played in the 3rd week of June 2014 by 25 different rock radio stations
